Bathtub: This is not the cleanest bathtub in the world, but it's cleaner than you are right now.
Perception (Smell): Ah, that soap scum smell. It smells like life. At least compared to you.
Savoir Faire: Hold it right there! Keep your head above water, or you'll lose all those pheromones Morell sprayed on you.
Bathtub: Now you are alone with your thoughts in the tub. But it's easier than being alone with your thoughts outside the tub.

Bathtub: The lukewarm water is comforting, like amniotic fluid.
Bathtub: The bathtub slowly fills with water. The water beckons.
You: Run yourself a bath.
Electrochemistry: They're not even really thoughts. Just assorted sensations, none of them acute enough to focus on.
You: Leave the beer cans in.
Inland Empire: You feel nice and lonely. And so, so tired.
You: Take the beer cans out.
You: Linger in the tub a little.
Physical Instrument: What are you doing? You're not some fat fish in a fucking aquarium. Time to get moving.
lingerhub
You: Get out. (Conclude.)
Bathtub: The water line recedes as you stand. You are cold now. Your clothes stick to your still moist skin.
Bathtub: The water doesn't feel particularly clean. A few beer cans are bobbing up and down along your flanks like sad duckies. You pause to think before letting your head go under.
You: Undress, close your eyes, and submerge.
You: I want to live forever with the corpse smell. Memento mori and stuff. [Leave.]
Bathtub: Your fingers grow pale and are covered with tiny whorls as the water cools.
You: I don't care. I just want to be engulfed.
bathtubhub
Bathtub: The cans continue to bob, as do your thoughts, aimlessly splashing up against the sides of the tub.
Conceptualization: Then -- houses along a narrow street. A video rental. Darkness on the planet's curvature.
Untitled hub
Bathtub: You see the corpse. You can still smell the cadaver on you. It's going to take more than one bath to get rid of that stench.
You: Imagine something.
You: Keep your head above water, just in case.
Bathtub: The water is only lukewarm, but still comforting, like amniotic fluid. A few beer cans are bobbing up and down along your flanks like sad duckies.
